# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Kamal secrets — this file is SAFE TO COMMIT.
#
# It never contains real secret values. Each line only *references* an
# environment variable that must already be set on the machine running
# `kamal deploy` (your laptop or a CI runner) — Kamal reads this file at
# deploy time and injects the resolved values into the remote containers
# over SSH; nothing is written to the server's disk in plaintext.
#
# Populate the referenced variables locally via a git-ignored `.env` file
# (see .env.example / dotenv-rails, already used elsewhere in this repo) or
# your CI secrets store (e.g. GitHub Actions `secrets.*`). See
# docs/deployment-guide/src/04_secrets-and-credentials.adoc for the full
# setup walkthrough, including a 1Password-based alternative.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# GitHub Container Registry credentials (matches .github/workflows/docker.yml).
# A GitHub Personal Access Token with `read:packages` scope works for pulling;
# use one with `write:packages` if you also build & push from this machine.
KAMAL_REGISTRY_USERNAME=$KAMAL_REGISTRY_USERNAME
KAMAL_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=$KAMAL_REGISTRY_PASSWORD

# Rails credentials key — same value as config/master.key. Required for the
# app to decrypt config/credentials.yml.enc at boot.
RAILS_MASTER_KEY=$RAILS_MASTER_KEY

# Application database (see config/database.yml — production.primary.password).
HEADLESS_DAM_DATABASE_PASSWORD=$HEADLESS_DAM_DATABASE_PASSWORD

# Same value, passed to the Postgres accessory container as POSTGRES_PASSWORD
# so the app's connection password and the accessory's own password match.
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=$HEADLESS_DAM_DATABASE_PASSWORD
